{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"There's a lot of exciting things happening in the design world"},{"time":2000,"text":"and at IDEO this past year,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and I'm pleased to get a chance to share some of those with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10000,"text":"I didn't attend the first TED back in 1984"},{"time":14000,"text":"but I've been to a lot of them since that time."},{"time":16000,"text":"I thought it [would] kind of be interesting to think back to that time"},{"time":20000,"text":"when Richard got the whole thing started. Thank you very much, Richard;"},{"time":23000,"text":"it's been a big, enjoyable part of my life, coming here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26000,"text":"And so thinking back, I was thinking"},{"time":29000,"text":"those of us in Silicon Valley were really focused on products or objects --"},{"time":35000,"text":"certainly technological objects."},{"time":37000,"text":"And so it was great fun in those days, and some of those of you"},{"time":42000,"text":"who are in the audience were my clients."},{"time":44000,"text":"We'd come in with some prototype underneath a black cloth"},{"time":48000,"text":"and we'd put it on the conference table,"},{"time":50000,"text":"and we'd pull off the black cloth and everybody would \"ooh\" and \"ah.\""},{"time":54000,"text":"That was a really good time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"And so we'll continue to focus on products, as we always have."},{"time":60000,"text":"And if you were here last year,"},{"time":64000,"text":"I probably wrestled you to the floor and tried to show you my new EyeModule 2,"},{"time":69000,"text":"which was a camera that plugged into the Handspring."},{"time":73000,"text":"And I took a lot of pictures last year;"},{"time":75000,"text":"very few people knew what I was up to, but I took a lot of pictures."},{"time":78000,"text":"This year -- maybe you could show the slides --"},{"time":83000,"text":"this year we're carrying this Treo, which we had a lot to do with"},{"time":86000,"text":"and helped Handspring design it."},{"time":88000,"text":"Also, though we designed it a few years ago --"},{"time":91000,"text":"it's just become ubiquitous in the last year or so --"},{"time":93000,"text":"this Heartstream defibrillator which is saving lives."},{"time":95000,"text":"Maybe you've seen them in the airports? They seem to be everywhere now."},{"time":98000,"text":"Lots of lives are being saved by those."},{"time":100000,"text":"And, we're just about to announce the Zinio Reader product"},{"time":106000,"text":"that I believe will make magazines even more enjoyable to read."},{"time":110000,"text":"So, we really will continue to focus on products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113000,"text":"But something's happened in the last 18 years since Richard started TED,"},{"time":117000,"text":"and that's that people like us --"},{"time":119000,"text":"I know people in other places have caught onto this for a long time,"},{"time":122000,"text":"but for us, we've really just started ... we've kind of"},{"time":128000,"text":"climbed Maslow's hierarchy a little bit --"},{"time":131000,"text":"and so we're now focused more and more on human-centered design,"},{"time":135000,"text":"human-centeredness in an approach to design."},{"time":140000,"text":"That really involves designing behaviors and personality into products."},{"time":145000,"text":"And I think you're starting to see that,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and it's making our job even more enjoyable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"Interestingly enough, we used to primarily build 3-D models --"},{"time":156000,"text":"you know, you've seen some today -- and 3-D renderings."},{"time":160000,"text":"Then we'd go and we'd show those as communicating our ideas."},{"time":164000,"text":"But firms like ours are having to move to a point where"},{"time":167000,"text":"we get those objects that we're designing and get them in motion,"},{"time":171000,"text":"showing how they'll be used."},{"time":173000,"text":"And so in order to do that we've been forming"},{"time":177000,"text":"internal video-production groups"},{"time":180000,"text":"in order to make these kind of experience prototypes"},{"time":183000,"text":"that show just what we mean about the man-machine relationship."},{"time":187000,"text":"And it's a much better way to see."},{"time":189000,"text":"It's kind of like architects who show people in their houses,"},{"time":192000,"text":"as opposed to them being empty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194000,"text":"So I thought that I would show you a few videos"},{"time":198000,"text":"to show off this new, broader definition"},{"time":205000,"text":"of design in products and services and environments."},{"time":209000,"text":"I have a few of them -- they're no more than a minute"},{"time":212000,"text":"or a minute-and-a-half apiece --"},{"time":214000,"text":"but I thought you might be interested in seeing some of our"},{"time":217000,"text":"work over the last year, and how it responds in video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222000,"text":"So, Prada New York: we were asked by Rem Koolhaas"},{"time":225000,"text":"and OMA to help us conceive the technology"},{"time":229000,"text":"that's in their retail store in New York."},{"time":232000,"text":"He wanted a new kind of store -- a new one --"},{"time":234000,"text":"a store that had a cultural role as well as a retail one."},{"time":239000,"text":"And that meant actually designing custom technology"},{"time":243000,"text":"as opposed to just buying things off the shelf and putting them to use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"So, there're lots of things. Everything has RF tags:"},{"time":250000,"text":"there's RF tags on the user, on the cards,"},{"time":253000,"text":"there's the staff devices that are all around the store."},{"time":256000,"text":"You pick them up, and once you see something that you're interested in,"},{"time":259000,"text":"the staff person can scan them in"},{"time":261000,"text":"and then they can be shown on any screen throughout the store."},{"time":264000,"text":"You can look at color, and sizes, and how it appeared on the runway, or whatever."},{"time":270000,"text":"And so then the object -- the merchandise that you're interested in --"},{"time":274000,"text":"can be scanned. It's taken into the dressing room,"},{"time":277000,"text":"and in the dressing room there are scanners"},{"time":279000,"text":"so that we know exactly what clothing you have in the dressing room."},{"time":284000,"text":"We can put that up on a touch screen"},{"time":287000,"text":"and you can play with that, and get more information"},{"time":289000,"text":"about the clothing that you're interested in as you're trying it on."},{"time":294000,"text":"It's been used a lot of places, but I particularly like the use here"},{"time":298000,"text":"of liquid crystal displays in the changing room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"The last time I went to see this store,"},{"time":304000,"text":"there was a huge buzz about people standing outside and wondering,"},{"time":307000,"text":"\"Am I going to actually get to see the people changing clothes here?\""},{"time":310000,"text":"But if you push the button, of course, the whole wall goes dark."},{"time":315000,"text":"So you can try to get approval, or not, for whatever you're wearing."},{"time":323000,"text":"And then one of my favorite features of the technology"},{"time":326000,"text":"is the magic mirror, where you put on the clothes."},{"time":328000,"text":"There's a big display in the mirror, and you can turn around --"},{"time":332000,"text":"but there's a three second delay."},{"time":334000,"text":"So you can see what you look like from the back or all the way around, as you look."},{"time":338000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"About a year and a half ago we were asked to design"},{"time":365000,"text":"an installation in the museum --"},{"time":367000,"text":"this is a new wing of the Science Museum in London,"},{"time":370000,"text":"and it's primarily about digital and biomedical issues."},{"time":374000,"text":"And a group at Itch, which is now part of IDEO,"},{"time":378000,"text":"designed this interactive wall that's about four stories tall."},{"time":381000,"text":"I don't know if anybody's seen this --"},{"time":382000,"text":"it's pretty spectacular in the room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"Anyway, it's based on the London subway system."},{"time":386000,"text":"And so you can see that"},{"time":389000,"text":"the goal is to bring some of the feedback"},{"time":391000,"text":"that the people who had gone to the museum were giving,"},{"time":394000,"text":"and get it up on the wall so everybody could see. Just for everybody to see."},{"time":397000,"text":"So you enter your information. Then, like the London tube system,"},{"time":401000,"text":"the little trains go around with what you're thinking about."},{"time":406000,"text":"And then when you get to a station, it's expanded so that you can actually read it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411000,"text":"Then when you exit the IMAX theatre on the fourth floor --"},{"time":415000,"text":"mostly teenagers coming out of there --"},{"time":417000,"text":"there's this big open space that has these tables in it"},{"time":421000,"text":"that have interactive games which are quite fun,"},{"time":423000,"text":"also designed by Durrell [Bishop] and Andrew [Hirniak] of Itch."},{"time":425000,"text":"And the topics include things that the museum is about:"},{"time":431000,"text":"male fertility, choosing the sex of your baby"},{"time":434000,"text":"or what a driverless car might be like."},{"time":438000,"text":"There's lots of room, so people can come up"},{"time":440000,"text":"and understand what it is before they get involved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444000,"text":"And also, it's not shown in the video, but these are very beautiful."},{"time":446000,"text":"They go to the top of the wall and when they reach all the way to the top,"},{"time":450000,"text":"after they've bounced around, they disperse into bits"},{"time":453000,"text":"and go off into the atmosphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"The next video is not done by us."},{"time":461000,"text":"This is CBS Sunday Morning that aired about two weeks ago."},{"time":465000,"text":"Scott Adams ran into us"},{"time":467000,"text":"and asked us if we wouldn't help to design"},{"time":469000,"text":"the ultimate cubicle for Dilbert,"},{"time":471000,"text":"which sounded like a fun thing and so we couldn't pass it up."},{"time":475000,"text":"He's always been interested in technology in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"(Video: Scott Adams: I realized that at some point I might be"},{"time":480000,"text":"the world's expert on what's wrong with cubicles."},{"time":483000,"text":"So we thought, well, wouldn't it be fun to get together"},{"time":485000,"text":"with some of the smartest design guys in the world"},{"time":487000,"text":"and try to figure out if we could make the cubicle better?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":490000,"text":"Narrator: Though they work in a wide-open office space"},{"time":493000,"text":"spectacularly set under San Francisco's Oakland Bay Bridge,"},{"time":498000,"text":"the team built their own little cubicles"},{"time":500000,"text":"to fully experience the problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503000,"text":"Woman: A one-way mirror. I can look out; you can look at yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506000,"text":"Narrator: They took pictures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507000,"text":"Woman: You feel so trapped, when someone kind of leans over"},{"time":510000,"text":"and you're sort of held captive there for a minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"SA: So far it's chaos, but a lot of people are doing stuff, so that's good."},{"time":516000,"text":"We'll see what happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518000,"text":"Narrator: The first group builds a cubicle in which the walls are screens"},{"time":522000,"text":"for the computer and for family photos."},{"time":525000,"text":"In the second group's scenario, the walls are alive"},{"time":529000,"text":"and actually give Dilbert a group hug."},{"time":532000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":534000,"text":"Behind the humor is the idea of making the cubicle more human.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":540000,"text":"David Kelley: So here's the final thing, complete with orange lighting"},{"time":543000,"text":"that follows the sun across -- that follows the tracks of the sun -- across the sky."},{"time":547000,"text":"So you feel that in your cubicle."},{"time":551000,"text":"And my favorite feature, which is a flower in a vase"},{"time":553000,"text":"that wilts when you leave in disappointment,"},{"time":556000,"text":"and then when you come back, it comes up to greet you, happy to see you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560000,"text":"(SA: The storage is built right into the wall.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":562000,"text":"DK: You know, it has homey touches like a built-in fish tank in the walls,"},{"time":567000,"text":"or something to be aggressive with to release tension."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571000,"text":"(SA: Customizable for the boss of your choice.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"DK: And of course: a hammock for your afternoon nap"},{"time":577000,"text":"that stretches across your cubicle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579000,"text":"(SA: Life would be sweet in a cubicle like this.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"DK: This next project, we were asked to design a pavilion to celebrate"},{"time":590000,"text":"the recycling of the water on the Millennium Dome in London."},{"time":594000,"text":"The dome has an incredible amount of water that washes off of it,"},{"time":597000,"text":"as well as wastewater."},{"time":599000,"text":"So this building actually celebrates the water"},{"time":602000,"text":"as it comes out of the recycling plant and goes into the reed bed"},{"time":605000,"text":"so that it can be filtered for the final time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610000,"text":"The pavilion's design goal was to be kind of quiet and peaceful."},{"time":614000,"text":"In contrast to if you went inside the dome, where it's"},{"time":617000,"text":"kind of wild and crazy and everybody's"},{"time":619000,"text":"learning all kinds of things, or fooling around, or whatever they're doing."},{"time":622000,"text":"But it was intended to be quite quiet."},{"time":625000,"text":"And then you would wander around and gather information,"},{"time":629000,"text":"in a straightforward fashion, about the recycling process"},{"time":633000,"text":"and what's being done, and how they're going to reuse the water"},{"time":636000,"text":"once it comes through the plant."},{"time":647000,"text":"And then, if you saw,"},{"time":649000,"text":"the panels actually rotate. So you can get the information"},{"time":652000,"text":"on the front side, but as they rotate, you can see the actual"},{"time":655000,"text":"recycling plant behind, with all the machines as they actually process the water."},{"time":665000,"text":"You can see: there's the plant."},{"time":676000,"text":"These are all very low-budget videos, like quick prototypes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680000,"text":"And we're announcing a new product here tonight,"},{"time":682000,"text":"which is the first time this has ever been shown in public."},{"time":685000,"text":"It's called Spyfish, and it's a company called H2Eye,"},{"time":690000,"text":"started by Nigel Jagger in London."},{"time":693000,"text":"And it's a company that's trying to bring the experience -- many people have boats,"},{"time":699000,"text":"or enjoy being on boats, but a very small percentage of people"},{"time":704000,"text":"actually have the capability or the interest in going under the water"},{"time":709000,"text":"and actually seeing what's there,"},{"time":711000,"text":"and enjoying what scuba divers do."},{"time":713000,"text":"This product, it has two cameras."},{"time":715000,"text":"You throw it over the side of your boat"},{"time":718000,"text":"and you basically scuba dive without getting wet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"For us -- there's the object -- for us, it was two projects. One, to design the interface"},{"time":731000,"text":"so that the interface doesn't get in your way."},{"time":733000,"text":"You could have that kind of immersive experience of being underwater --"},{"time":736000,"text":"of feeling like you're underwater -- seeing what's going on."},{"time":739000,"text":"And the other one was to design the object"},{"time":741000,"text":"and make sure that it was a consumer product and not a research tool."},{"time":746000,"text":"And so we spent a lot of time -- this has been going on for about"},{"time":748000,"text":"seven or eight years, this project --"},{"time":750000,"text":"and [we're] just ready to start building them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756000,"text":"(Narrator: The Spyfish is a revolutionary subaquatic video camera."},{"time":760000,"text":"It can dive to 500 feet, to where sunlight does not penetrate,"},{"time":763000,"text":"and is equipped with powerful lights."},{"time":766000,"text":"It becomes your eyes and ears as you venture into the deep."},{"time":771000,"text":"The battery-powered Spyfish sends the live video-feed through a slender cable.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"DK: This slender cable was a huge technological advancement"},{"time":778000,"text":"and it allowed the whole thing to be the size that it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780000,"text":"(Narrator: And this central box connects the whole system together."},{"time":783000,"text":"Maneuvering the Spyfish is simple with the wireless remote control."},{"time":787000,"text":"You watch the video with superimposed graphics"},{"time":789000,"text":"that indicate your depth and compass heading."},{"time":793000,"text":"The fluid graphics and ambient sounds combine"},{"time":795000,"text":"to help you completely lose yourself underwater.)"},{"time":819000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"DK: And the last thing I'll talk about is ApproTEC,"},{"time":828000,"text":"which is a project that I'm very excited about."},{"time":831000,"text":"ApproTEC is a company started by Dr. Martin Fisher,"},{"time":834000,"text":"who's a good friend of mine. He's a Ph.D. from Stanford."},{"time":837000,"text":"He found himself in Kenya on a Fulbright"},{"time":840000,"text":"and he had a very interesting insight, which is that"},{"time":842000,"text":"he said, \"There must be entrepreneurs in Kenya;"},{"time":846000,"text":"there must be entrepreneurs everywhere.\""},{"time":848000,"text":"And he noticed that for weddings and funerals there"},{"time":851000,"text":"they could find enough money to put something together."},{"time":854000,"text":"So he decided to start manufacturing products in Kenya"},{"time":858000,"text":"with Kenyan manufacturers -- designed by people like us, but taken there."},{"time":863000,"text":"And to this date -- he's been gone for only a few years --"},{"time":866000,"text":"he's started 19,000 companies."},{"time":870000,"text":"He's made 30,000 new jobs."},{"time":873000,"text":"And just the sales of the products -- this is a non-profit --"},{"time":878000,"text":"the sales of these products is now .6% of the GDP of Kenya."},{"time":884000,"text":"This is one guy doing this. This is a pretty spectacular thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"So we're in the process of helping them design"},{"time":890000,"text":"deep-well, low-cost manual pumps"},{"time":893000,"text":"in order for these people who have a quarter acre of land"},{"time":897000,"text":"to be able to grow crops in the off-season."},{"time":899000,"text":"What they do now is: they can grow crops in the rainy season"},{"time":901000,"text":"but they can't grow them in the off-season."},{"time":904000,"text":"And so by doing that, the woman that you saw in the first thing --"},{"time":908000,"text":"she's a school teacher -- always wanted to send her kids to college"},{"time":912000,"text":"and she's going to be able to do it because of these things."},{"time":914000,"text":"So with seed-squeezers, and pumps, and hay-balers and"},{"time":917000,"text":"very straightforward things that we're designing --"},{"time":920000,"text":"my students are doing this as class projects"},{"time":922000,"text":"and IDEO has donated their time to do this kind of work --"},{"time":925000,"text":"it's really amazing to see his success, Martin's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929000,"text":"We also were thinking about the experience of Richard,"},{"time":934000,"text":"and so --"},{"time":935000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":936000,"text":"-- we designed this hat, because I knew I'd be the last one in the day"},{"time":941000,"text":"and I needed to deal with him. So I just have one more thing to say."},{"time":945000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":948000,"text":"Can you read it?"},{"time":950000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":951000,"text":"Well, it's always kind of funny when he comes up and hovers."},{"time":954000,"text":"You know, you don't want to be rude to him and you don't want to feel guilty,"},{"time":958000,"text":"and so I thought this would do it, where I just sit here."},{"time":961000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":962000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":970000,"text":"So we saw a lot of interesting things being designed today in this session,"},{"time":974000,"text":"and from all the different presenters."},{"time":977000,"text":"And in my own practice, from product to ApproTEC,"},{"time":981000,"text":"it's really exciting that we're taking a more human-centered approach to design,"},{"time":986000,"text":"that we're including behaviors and personalities in the things we do,"},{"time":989000,"text":"and I think this is great."},{"time":991000,"text":"Designers are more trusted and more integrated"},{"time":993000,"text":"into the business strategy of companies,"},{"time":995000,"text":"and I have to say, for one, I feel very lucky at the progress that design"},{"time":1001000,"text":"has made since the first TED. Thanks a lot."}]}]}